<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 04 at 12:56AM MDT until July 04 at 7:00AM MDT by NWS Sioux Falls</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 215 AM CDT
FOR CENTRAL BRULE COUNTY...
At 156 AM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 8 miles east of Stephan to near Chamberlain to near
Iona, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Kimball.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
